---
Checks: >
  bugprone-*,
  cert-*,
  clang-analyzer-*,
  performance-*,
  portability-*,
  readability-*,
  -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters,
  -bugprone-implicit-widening-of-multiplication-result,
  -cert-err33-c,
  -cert-msc30-c,
  -cert-msc32-c,
  -clang-analyzer-security.insecureAPI.DeprecatedOrUnsafeBufferHandling,
  -performance-no-int-to-ptr,
  -readability-function-cognitive-complexity,
  -readability-identifier-length,
  -readability-inconsistent-declaration-parameter-name,
  -readability-magic-numbers,
  -readability-named-parameter,
  -readability-qualified-auto,
  -readability-uppercase-literal-suffix
WarningsAsErrors: '*'
HeaderFilterRegex: '^(src|include|tests)/(?!property/vendor/theft).*'
FormatStyle: file
CheckOptions:
  - key: readability-function-size.LineThreshold
    value: '120'
...

# Disabled checks:
# - bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters: allocator and test callbacks intentionally use adjacent
#   pointer/size parameters matching C library conventions.
# - bugprone-implicit-widening-of-multiplication-result: property generators use small bounded
#   compile-time constants where widening is explicit in the receiving API.
# - cert-err33-c: tests deliberately assert behavior around allocator failures and do not need to
#   branch on every printf-like helper in failure-message paths.
# - cert-msc30-c/cert-msc32-c: the vendored theft runner uses an explicit deterministic RNG instead
#   of rand; the check is noisy around env-seeded property tests.
# - clang-analyzer-security.insecureAPI.DeprecatedOrUnsafeBufferHandling: diagnostics point at
#   fprintf/snprintf in test failure messages, not production buffer handling.
# - performance-no-int-to-ptr: vector tests intentionally use integer-shaped opaque pointer values
#   without dereferencing them.
# - readability-function-cognitive-complexity/readability-function-size: fuzz and property tests are
#   intentionally branch-heavy to cover operation streams.
# - readability-identifier-length: C APIs and tests use conventional short names such as ctx and i.
# - readability-inconsistent-declaration-parameter-name: Criterion's Test macro expands to generated
#   function declarations that look inconsistent to clang-tidy.
# - readability-magic-numbers: test data and fuzz operation tags are clearer inline.
# - readability-named-parameter: public typedef docs describe callback arguments.
# - readability-qualified-auto: not relevant to C.
# - readability-uppercase-literal-suffix: the codebase uses the conventional lowercase C suffix style.
